    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc_es.00034.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener> 
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place"><handShift rend="printed"/>Superintendent's Office.</name>
                    <name type="place">Asylum<lb/>for the Insane</name>
                    <name type="place">London.</name>
                    <name type="place">Ontario</name>
                    <name type="place">London, Ont.,</name>
                    <date when="1889-01-01"><handShift rend="manuscript"/>1 Jan <handShift rend="printed"/>188<handShift rend="manuscript"/>9<ptr target="loc.04982_n2"/></date>
                </dateline>
            </opener> 
            <p>Your card of 30<hi rend="underline">th</hi><ptr target="loc.04982_n1"/> to hand this
                forenoon. I am glad you are holding out but I fear you are not having a very good
                time. We had a young peoples' party at the home last night and they danced the new
                year in. We were very merry (as old Pepys would say) but it makes a fellow feel rather stupid
                next day. Was a lovely bright forenoon, clouded over now. Nesbit<ptr target="n4153"/> is here since
                yesterday afternoon, he, Gurd<ptr target="n4284"/> and I consulting over the meter—not sure yet
                what our next step in advance will be. I enclose a note from Mrs Pardee<ptr target="loc.04982_n3"/> wh may
                interest you—</p>
            <closer> 
                <salute>Your friend</salute>
                <signed>R M Bucke</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc_es.00033.jpg" type="verso"/>
        </body>
    </text>
